Step 1. Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Total Liabilities: In the balance sheet, the only liabilities provided are the current liabilities.  
  Total Liabilities = 728279.50  
• Total Owner’s Equity = 14095371.35  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity  
  = 728279.50 / 14095371.35 ≈ 0.0517, rounded to 0.05  

Step 2. Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• Net Profit (from income statement) = 1095371.35  
• Total Revenue = 5565589.48  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (1095371.35 / 5565589.48) × 100 ≈ 19.67%  

Step 3. Calculate Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities (from cash flow statement) = -81548.37  
• Total Current Liabilities = 728279.50  
• Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
  = -81548.37 / 728279.50 ≈ -0.112, rounded to -0.11  

Thus, the final solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.05",
    "Net Profit Margin": "19.67%",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-0.11"
  }
}
